<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10601] SecondaryIndexManager incorrectly updates index build status system table</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10601</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;markIndexBuilt&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;markIndexRemoved&lt;/tt&gt; methods on &lt;tt&gt;SecondaryIndexManager&lt;/tt&gt; incorrectly supply the table name to the methods on &lt;tt&gt;SystemKeyspace&lt;/tt&gt; which update the underlying system table. They should pass the keyspace name instead, which results in incorrect rows being written to/removed from the system table when a rebuild of the index is performed. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12908254">CASSANDRA-10601</key>
