                            <comment id="14976536" author="beobal" created="Tue, 27 Oct 2015 15:11:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed a branch with a fix &amp;amp; a unit test for this, which also exposes the 2 &lt;tt&gt;markIndexXXX&lt;/tt&gt;} methods on &lt;tt&gt;SIM&lt;/tt&gt; so that index implementations can call them after performing an initial build. &lt;tt&gt;CassandraIndex&lt;/tt&gt; was duplicating this functionality (albeit without the bug), in its &lt;tt&gt;buildBlocking&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s another &lt;tt&gt;SIM&lt;/tt&gt; bug that can be cleaned up here; The call to &lt;tt&gt;unregisterIndex&lt;/tt&gt; from &lt;tt&gt;removeIndex&lt;/tt&gt; is unnecessary as the index has already be removed from the collection of known indexes earlier in the method. This is mostly harmless, but it will result in an erroneous log message at &lt;tt&gt;TRACE&lt;/tt&gt; level. &lt;/p&gt;

